# Nikto Command Cheatsheet (With Meanings)

Nikto is an open-source web server vulnerability scanner used to identify
misconfigurations, outdated software, and common web vulnerabilities.

---

## ğŸ” Basic Scanning Commands

### Scan a website
```bash
nikto -h http://example.com
Meaning:
Scans the target website for common vulnerabilities and server issues.

Scan using IP address
nikto -h 192.168.1.10
Meaning:
Runs a Nikto scan directly on a server using its IP address.

Scan a specific port
nikto -h example.com -p 8080
Meaning:
Scans the web service running on port 8080 instead of the default port.

ğŸ” HTTPS / SSL Commands
Scan HTTPS website
nikto -h https://example.com
Meaning:
Scans a website that uses SSL/TLS (HTTPS).

Force SSL scan
nikto -h example.com -ssl
Meaning:
Forces Nikto to treat the target as an SSL-enabled website.

ğŸ“‚ Output & Reporting
Save output to a text file
nikto -h example.com -o result.txt
Meaning:
Stores scan results in a text file for documentation.

Save output in HTML format
nikto -h example.com -o report.html -Format html
Meaning:
Generates a browser-readable HTML vulnerability report.

Save output in JSON format
nikto -h example.com -o report.json -Format json
Meaning:
Exports scan results in JSON format for automation or analysis.

ğŸ¯ Target Customization
Scan multiple ports
nikto -h example.com -p 80,443,8080
Meaning:
Scans multiple web services running on different ports.

Use a custom User-Agent
nikto -h example.com -useragent Mozilla/5.0
Meaning:
Makes Nikto appear as a normal browser to bypass basic filters.

Use proxy (Burp/ZAP)
nikto -h example.com -useproxy http://127.0.0.1:8080
Meaning:
Routes Nikto traffic through a proxy for inspection.

âš™ï¸ Scan Tuning
Tune scan types
nikto -h example.com -Tuning 123
Meaning:
Runs only selected categories of vulnerability checks.

Tuning Codes:

1 â€“ Interesting files

2 â€“ Misconfiguration

3 â€“ Default files

4 â€“ Injection

5 â€“ XSS

Scan only Injection & XSS
nikto -h example.com -Tuning 4,5
Meaning:
Focuses only on Injection and Cross-Site Scripting vulnerabilities.

ğŸš€ Advanced Commands
Update Nikto database
nikto -update
Meaning:
Updates vulnerability signatures and plugins.

Virtual host scan
nikto -h example.com -vhost test.example.com
Meaning:
Scans a specific virtual host hosted on the same server.

Use IDS evasion technique
nikto -h example.com -evasion 1
Meaning:
Attempts to bypass intrusion detection systems.

ğŸ›¡ï¸ Stealth & Safety
Slow scan to avoid detection
nikto -h example.com -delay 5
Meaning:
Adds a delay between requests to reduce detection chances.

Disable DNS lookup
nikto -h example.com -nodns
Meaning:
Prevents DNS resolution to speed up scanning.

ğŸ“ One-Line Summary
Nikto is used in VAPT to detect web server misconfigurations, insecure files,
outdated software, and common web vulnerabilities.
